                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00/256: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Callao-Lima</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Handley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-05T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 5, 1919, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received July 6, 10.02 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Provisional President Leguia’s Cabinet, headed by Doctor Meliton Porras formerly
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs during Leguia’s former administration, is composed
                    of highly esteemed statesmen and business men who enjoy national respect. All
                    the provinces have accepted new Government including the military and naval
                    authorities. Alfonso Pezet, formerly Peruvian Minister to the United States,
                    will probably be named Ambassador to the United States. He will arrive here July
                    10th. This afternoon Government established censor[ship] on foreign cables.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Handley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
